==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trenchmore
<hw>Trench"more</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A kind of lively
dance of a rude, boisterous character. Also, music in triple time
appropriate to the dance.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the windows in the town dance new <qex>trenchmore</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trenchmore</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Trenchmore
<hw>Trench"more</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To dance the
trenchmore.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Marston.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

